`WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated because Android removed `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` in API 30. In .NET 10 MAUI, use **window insets** to react to the keyboard (IME) instead.

### Recommended approach: Adjust padding via insets (Android)

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    // Let content draw behind the keyboard area
    WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

    var content = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new InsetsListener());
}

private class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset
        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

### iOS

iOS handles this automatically via `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (enabled by default in MAUI). If it's not working, ensure you haven't disabled it:

```csharp
// In MauiProgram.cs — only if you previously disabled it
builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(h =>
{
    Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect = true;
});
```

### Tips for chat layouts

- Wrap your message list + input bar in a `Grid`, not a `StackLayout`.
- Put the input bar in the **last row** with `GridRow="1" VerticalOptions="End"`.
- The insets listener above will push the entire content up by the keyboard height, keeping your input bar visible.
